obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (3560)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. The words "except the State of Hyderabad" omitted by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980&sectionId=3560&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Territorial Army Act, 1948.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1* * * and applies to all classes of persons in the Territorial Army,`
  line `wherever they may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (3561)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980&sectionId=3561&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(a) "enrolled" means enrolled in the Territorial Army under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "officer" means an officer of any of the two classes specified in section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) "non-commissioned officer" means a person holding a non-commissioned rank in the`
  line `Territorial Army, and includes an acting non-commissioned officer;`
  line
  line `(d) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `^1[(dd) "public utility service" means any undertaking which supplies power, light, gas or water to`
  line `the public, or carries on a public transport, or maintains any system of public conservancy or`
  line `sanitation and which is declared, by notification in the Official Gazette, by the Central Government to`
  line `be a public utility service to which this Act applies:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such modification shall be issued unless the Central Government is satisfied`
  line `that, having regard to the needs of the Territorial Army, the persons employed in any such public`
  line `utility service should, in the public interest, be made compulsorily liable for service in that Army`
  line `under this Act;]`
  line
  line `(e) the expression ^2[Regular Army] means officers and other ranks who, by their commission,`
  line `terms of enrolment or otherwise, are liable to render continuously for a term military service under`
  line `^3[the Army Act, 1950 (46 of 1950)]; and`
  line
  line `(f) all words and expressions used herein and defined in ^3[the Army Act, 1950 (46 of 1950)], and`
  line `not hereinbefore defined, shall be deemed to have the meanings respectively attributed to them by`
  line `that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 92 of 1956, s. 2.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "regular forces".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "the Indian Army Act, 1911".`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (3562)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of the Territorial Army.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980&sectionId=3562&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be raised and maintained in the manner`
  line `hereinafter provided an army to be designated the Territorial Army.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may constitute such number of units of the Territorial Army as it thinks`
  line `fit and may disband or reconstitute any unit so constituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (3563)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Personnel of the Territorial Army.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980&sectionId=3563&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `There shall be the following classes of persons in the`
  line `Territorial Army, namely,--`
  line
  line `(a) officers; and`
  line
  line `(b) enrolled persons.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (3564)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title Officers.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980&sectionId=3564&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Officers in the Territorial Army shall be of the two following classes, namely,--`
  line
  line `(a) officers holding commissions in the Territorial Army granted by the President with`
  line `designations of rank corresponding to those of Indian commissioned officers ^1[of the Regular Army];`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) junior commissioned officers holding commissions in the Territorial Army granted by the`
  line `President with designations of rank corresponding to those of ^2[junior commissioned officers of the`
  line `Regular Army.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by the A.O. 1950.`
  line
  line `2. Subs., ibid., for "Viceroy's commissioned officers".`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (3565)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Persons eligible for enrolment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs.,ibid., for "Any person domiciled in India".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980&sectionId=3565&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[Any person who is a citizen of India] may offer himself for`
  line `enrolment in the Territorial Army, and may, if he satisfies the prescribed conditions, be enrolled for such`
  line `period and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_a:
  sectionId (3566)
  sectionNo 6A
  orderNo 7
  title `Liability of certain persons for compulsory service in the Territorial Army.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 92 of 1956, s. 3.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980&sectionId=3566&sectionno=6A&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[6A. Liability of certain persons for compulsory service in the Territorial Army.--(1) Without`
  line `prejudice to the provision contained in section 6, every person employed under the Government or in a`
  line `public utility service who has attained the age of twenty years but has not completed the age of forty years`
  line `shall, subject to the other provisions contained in this section and subject to such rules as may be made in`
  line `this behalf, be liable, when so required to do, to perform service in the Territorial Army.`
  line
  line `(2) Where it appears to the prescribed authority that, having regard to the strength of the Territorial`
  line `Army or of any unit thereof in any area or place or, having regard to the exigencies of service in the`
  line `Territorial Army, it is necessary that persons compulsorily liable to perform service in the Territorial`
  line `Army under sub-section (1) should be called upon for such service, the prescribed authority may call`
  line `upon such number of persons as he thinks fit for the purpose of performing service in the Territorial`
  line Army.
  line
  line `(3) In requisitioning the services of any persons under sub-section (2), the prescribed authority shall`
  line `have regard to the age, physical fitness, qualifications and experience of the persons to be called upon for`
  line `service and the nature of the work previously performed by them while employed under the Government`
  line `or in the public utility service, and the work to be performed by them in the Territorial Army.`
  line
  line `(4) Every person liable to perform service under sub-section (1) shall, if so required by the prescribed`
  line `authority, be bound to fill up such norms as may be prescribed and sign and lodge them with the`
  line `prescribed authority within such time as may be specified in the requisition.`
  line
  line `(5) The prescribed authority may require any person incharge of the management of a public utility`
  line `service to furnish within such time as may be specified in the requisition such particulars as may be`
  line `prescribed with respect to persons employed under him, who may be liable to perform service under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(6) Any person whose services are requisitioned under this section may be required to join the`
  line `Territorial Army as an officer or as an enrolled person according to the rules made in this behalf by the`
  line `Central Government, and where any person has so jointed the Territorial Army, he shall be entitled to the`
  line `same rights and privileges and be subject to the same liabilities as an officer or enrolled person under the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expression "person employed under the`
  line `Government or in a public utility service" shall not include--`
  line
  line `(a) a woman;`
  line
  line `(b) a member of the Regular Army, the Navy or the Air Force or a member of any Reserve Force;`
  line
  line `(c) a person who is not a citizen of India;`
  line
  line `(d) a person employed under the Government in any country or place outside India for so long as`
  line `he is so employed; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other persons as may be exempted from the operation of this Act by the Central`
  line `Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, on the ground that, having regard to the nature of`
  line `the service performed by such persons or to the exigencies of the service in which they are employed,`
  line `it is, in the opinion of the Central Government, expedient in the public interest that they should not be`
  line `liable to perform service under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (3567)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Liability for military service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980&sectionId=3567&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) No officer or enrolled person shall be required to perform`
  line `military service beyond the limits of India save under a general or special order of the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1), every officer or enrolled person shall, subject to such`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed, be bound to serve in any unit of the Territorial Army to which he is for`
  line `the time being attached, and shall be subject to all the rules made under this Act in relation to such unit.`
  line
  line `(3) Every officer or enrolled person shall be liable to perform military service,--`
  line
  line `(a) when called out in the prescribed manner to act in support of the civil power or to provide`
  line `essential guards;`
  line
  line `(b) when embodied in the prescribed manner for training or for supporting or supplementing the`
  line `regular forces; and`
  line
  line `(c) when attached to any regular forces either at his own request or under the prescribed`
  line conditions.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7_a:
  sectionId (3568)
  sectionNo 7A
  orderNo 9
  title `Reinstatement in civil employ of persons required to perform military service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 1952, s. 2`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980&sectionId=3568&sectionno=7A&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[7A. Reinstatement in civil employ of persons required to perform military service.--(1) It shall`
  line `be the duty of every employer by whom a person who is required to perform military service under`
  line `section 7 was employed to reinstate him in his employment on the termination of the military service in`
  line `an occupation and under conditions not less favourable to him than those which would have been`
  line `applicable to him had his employment not been so interrupted:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the employer refuses to reinstate such person or denies his liability to reinstate such`
  line `person, or if for any reason reinstatement of such person is represented by the employer to be`
  line `impracticable, either party may refer the matter to the prescribed authority and that authority shall, after`
  line `considering all matters which may be put before it and after making such further inquiry into the matter as`
  line `may be prescribed, pass an order--`
  line
  line `(a) exempting the employer from the provisions of this section, or`
  line
  line `(b) requiring him to re-employ such person on such terms as he thinks suitable, or`
  line
  line `(c) requiring him to pay to such person by way of compensation for failure or inability to`
  line `re-employ a sum not exceeding an amount equal to six months' remuneration at the rate at which his`
  line `last remuneration was payable to him by the employer.`
  line
  line `(2) If any employer fails to obey the order of any such authority as is referred to in the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (1), he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, and the court`
  line `by which an employer is convicted under this section shall order him (if he has not already been so`
  line `required by the said authority) to pay to the person whom he has failed to re-employ a sum equal to six`
  line `months' remuneration at the rate at which his last remuneration was payable to him by the employer, and`
  line `any amount so required to be paid either by the said authority or by the court shall be recoverable as if it`
  line `were a fine imposed by such court.`
  line
  line `(3) In any proceeding under this section it shall be a defence for an employer to prove that the person`
  line `formerly employed did not apply to the employer for reinstatement within a period of two months from`
  line `the termination of his military service.`
  line
  line `(4) The duty imposed by sub-section (1) upon an employer to reinstate in his employment a person`
  line `such as is described in that sub-section shall attach to an employer who, before such person is actually`
  line `required to perform military service under section 7, terminates his employment in circumstances such as`
  line `to indicate an intention to evade the duty imposed by that sub-section, and such intention shall be`
  line `presumed until the contrary is proved if the termination takes place after the issue of orders requiring him`
  line `to perform military service under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_b:
  sectionId (3569)
  sectionNo 7B
  orderNo 10
  title `Preservation of certain rights of persons required to perform military service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 1952, s. 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980&sectionId=3569&sectionno=7B&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980
obj_root_law_sections_7_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[7B. Preservation of certain rights of persons required to perform military service.--When any`
  line `person required to perform military service under section 7 has any rights under any provident fund or`
  line `superannuation fund or other scheme for the benefit of employees maintained in connection with the`
  line `employment he relinquishes, he shall continue, so long as he is engaged in military service and if he is`
  line `reinstated, until such reinstatement under the provisions of this Act, to have in respect of such fund or`
  line `scheme such rights as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (3570)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 11
  title Discharge.
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980&sectionId=3570&sectionno=8&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Every person enrolled under this Act shall be entitled to receive his discharge from`
  line `the Territorial Army on the expiration of the period for which he was enrolled and any such person may,`
  line `prior to the expiration of that period, be discharged from the said army by such authority and subject to`
  line `such conditions as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no enrolled person who is for the time being engaged in military service under the`
  line `provisions of this Act, shall be entitled to receive his discharge before the termination of such service.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (3571)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 12
  title `Application of the Army Act, 1950.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980&sectionId=3571&sectionno=9&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every officer, when doing duty as such officer, and`
  line `every enrolled person when called out or embodied or attached to ^1[the Regular Army], shall, subject to`
  line `such adaptations and modifications as may be made therein by the Central Government by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, be subject to the provisions of ^2[the Army Act, 1950 (46 of 1950)], and the rules or`
  line `regulations made thereunder in the same manner and to the same extent as if such officer or enrolled`
  line `person held the same rank in ^3[the Regular Army] as he holds for the time being in the Territorial Army.`
  line
  line `(2) When an offence punishable under ^2[the Army Act, 1950 (46 of 1950)], has been committed by`
  line `any person whilst subject to that Act under the provisions of sub-section (1) such person may be taken`
  line `into and kept in military custody and tried and punished for such offence as aforesaid in like manner as he`
  line `might have been taken into and kept in military custody, tried and punished if he had continued to be so`
  line subject.
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "any regular forces".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "the Indian Army Act, 1911".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "the regular forces".`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (3572)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 13
  title `Summary trial and punishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "the Indian Army Act, 1911".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980&sectionId=3572&sectionno=10&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `In addition to, or in substitution for, any punishment or`
  line `punishments to which he may be liable under ^1[the Army Act, 1950 (46 of 1950)], any enrolled person`
  line `may be punished either by a criminal Court or summarily by order of the prescribed authority for any`
  line `offence under that Act or for the contravention of any of the provisions of this Act or of any rules made`
  line `thereunder with fine which may extend to one hundred rupees to be recovered in such manner and by`
  line `such authority as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no fine shall be summarily inflicted by order of the prescribed authority in any case in`
  line `which the accused claims to be tried by a criminal Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (3573)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 14
  title `Punishment for failure to lodge forms duly filled up, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 92 of 1956, s. 4.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980&sectionId=3573&sectionno=10A&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[10A. Punishment for failure to lodge forms duly filled up, etc.--If any person fails without`
  line `sufficient cause--`
  line
  line `(a) to comply with any requisition under sub-section (4) or sub-section (5) of section 6A, or`
  line
  line `(b) to report himself for service when so required to do by the prescribed authority under`
  line `sub-section (2) of that section, or`
  line
  line `(c) to submit himself to medical or other examination when so called upon to do by the prescribed`
  line `authority under rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to three months, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to two hundred rupees, or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (3574)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 15
  title `Jurisdiction to try offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980&sectionId=3574&sectionno=11&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `No Court inferior to that of a Presidency Magistrate or a`
  line `Magistrate of the first class shall try any offence made punishable by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (3575)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 16
  title `Presumption as to certain documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980&sectionId=3575&sectionno=12&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Where an enrolled person is required by or in`
  line `pursuance of any rule made under this Act to attend at any place, a certificate purporting to be signed by`
  line `the prescribed officer stating that the person so required to attend failed to do so in accordance with such`
  line `requirement shall, without proof of the signature or appointment of such officer, be evidence of the`
  line `matters stated therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (3576)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 17
  title `Persons subject to this Act to be deemed part of regular forces for certain purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "regular forces".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980&sectionId=3576&sectionno=13&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line For
  line `the purposes of sections 128, 130 and 131 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), all`
  line `officers, non-commissioned officers and other enrolled persons who have been attached to a unit shall be`
  line `deemed to be officers, non-commissioned officers and soldiers for respectively of ^1[the Regular Army].`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (3577)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980&sectionId=3577&sectionno=14&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00001_194856_1517807318980
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may make rules to carry out the purposes of`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) prescribe the form under sub-section (4) of section 6A, the particulars that should be`
  line `furnished therein and which, and the period within which, the form should be lodged;`
  line
  line `(aa) prescribe the procedure for requiring persons liable for compulsory service in the Territorial`
  line `Army to be medically or otherwise examined with a view to determining whether they satisfy the`
  line `conditions imposed under this Act;]`
  line
  line `^2[(aaa)] prescribe the manner in which, and the period for which and the conditions subject to`
  line `which any person may be enrolled under this Act;`
  line `^3[or may be required to perform compulsory`
  line `service is the territorial Army]`
  line
  line `(b) prescribe the manner in which and the conditions subject to which officers and enrolled`
  line `persons may be called out for service, or embodied for training or for supporting or for supplementing`
  line `^4[the Regular Army] or attached to ^5[the Regular Army];`
  line
  line `(c) prescribe preliminary and periodical military training, compulsory and voluntary, for any`
  line `enrolled person and provide for the embodiment of any unit for that purpose;`
  line
  line `(d) define the manner in which and the conditions under which any enrolled person may be`
  line `excused from training ;`
  line
  line `^6[(dd) specify the authority for the purpose of the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 7A and the`
  line `manner in which any inquiry may be held by him;`
  line
  line `(ddd) define the rights under section 7B;]`
  line
  line `(e) prescribe the authorities by which and the conditions subject to which enrolled persons may`
  line `be discharged under section 8;`
  line
  line `(f) prescribe the authorities by which offences under this Act may be punished and the fine`
  line `inflicted may be recovered;`
  line
  line `(g) prescribe the officers by whom certificates may be signed under section 12;`
  line
  line `(h) generally provide for any other matter which under this Act is to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^7[(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 92 of 1956, s. 5.`
  line
  line `2. Clause (a) was relettered as (aaa) by s. 5, ibid.`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 5, ibid.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "the regular forces".`
  line
  line `5. Subs., ibid., for "any regular forces".`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 33 of 1952, s. 3.`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 53 of 1980, s. 2.`
